The paper discusses the design of communication systems using Terahertz (THz) bands, which involves statistical propagation and channel characterizations, adaptive transceiver designs, reconfigurable platforms, advanced signal processing algorithms and techniques along with upper layer protocols equipped with various security and privacy levels. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Multimedia (cs.MM), Augmented Reality (cs.AR), or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. However, since the paper primarily focuses on the statistical modeling of propagation channels for THz band, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
